Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
John Baptiste Yeon believed in community. He invested in Oregon, and in the infrastructure that connected people to meaningful places throughout the Pacific Northwest. A timber magnate, his marquee real estate development culminated in the Yeon. It was the tallest tower in Portland at the time of completion in 1911. The building was home to some of the most influential brands of the time including Woolworths and B.Dalton’s Books.

The Yeon has benefited from significant, recent improvements and renovations. New mechanical systems, restored historic windows, easy access bike storage, showers and lockers compliment move in ready, creative spaces. A thorough cosmetic update, completed in Summer 2020, brings a consistent, quality experience to all common areas of the property.
